Improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
There are areas within the code that can be of higher quality.

Improving code quality is important in making the code more readable
and easier to understand for anyone who reads the code.

Let's improve the quality of the code in order to be able to achieve
that goal,
* by minimizing scope of variables as much as possible
* by making happy paths more prominent whenever possible

Doing this is critical to improving the quality of the code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions into key parts of the code
commitResults.messageBody:
The code does not have any assertions statements within at this moment.

Assertions in Java are useful in order to determine whether the code
is working as intended or not.

Let's add in assertions into the existing code in order to ensure that
the code is working as intended at different points within the code.

The assertion statements are being added at key points to ensure that
the application is working as intended and can carry out what the task
it needs to do.

Add help functionality to the application
commitResults.messageBody:
When a user opens the application, it does not provide any prompts or
guide on how the application can be used. As such, the application
may seem intimidating and unfriendly to new users, or users who
have forgotten the commands.

Let's add,
* add a welcome message to make the user feel more welcome, as
well as introduce the help function to the user
* add a help function to the application to allow the user
to see all commands that the application has to offer

Doing this is important in order to allow new users to learn how to
use the application, while providing existing users a refresher
in case they have forgotten the commands needed to use the application.
